6D UML v0.1
framework: 6d-uml
phext-version: 0.4.3
generator: claude-max
system: phext-lattice + uml6d

UML is a standardized, graphical modeling language used by software developers and system architects to visualize, specify, construct, and document software systems.

6D UML is an extension to UML that enables us to track the life cycle of all software artifacts (inputs and outputs). The key design change is the introduction of a 5D asset ID and a stack of context panes.collection-map:
1: Meta
2: Requirements
3: Design
4: Source
5: Tests
6: Regressions
7: Docs
8: Whitepapers
9: Trainingdimension-map:
collection: SDLC Phase
volume: Sprint/Release
book: Module
chapter: Component
section: File
scroll: Unitmodule-registry:
