book.10: Web UI (phext_edit, uml6d_edit)dependency-map:
external:
  libphext 0.3.1: Coordinate types, delimiters, phokenize, explode/implode
  memmap2 0.9: Cross-platform memory-mapped file I/O
  rayon 1.10: Work-stealing parallelism
  serde 1 + serde_json 1: JSON serialization (web feature)
  ratatui 0.29 + crossterm 0.28: TUI rendering (tui feature)
  tempfile 3: Temporary file support
internal:
  uml6d -> index, mmap
  mmap -> index
  navigator -> coordinate_ext
  search -> index
  sentron -> index, coordinate_ext
  editor -> cursor, undo
  web_ui -> mmap, navigator, sentron, search, stats, uml6dR1 -- Core Engine
The foundation layer providing coordinate extensions and O(1) lattice indexing.
All other modules depend on Core for coordinate manipulation and content lookup.R1.1 -- Coordinate Extensions
- Hash + Eq + Ord for HashMap-based index
- Dimension enum mapping 1-9 keys to nine phext dimensions
- CoordinateNav trait: forward/backward in named dimension with lower-dim reset
- Peek movement without resetting lower dims
- Delimiter byte mapping for each dimension
- Value get/set for any dimension with clampingR1.2 -- Lattice Index
- Single O(n) scan builds HashMap<Coordinate, ScrollSpan>
- O(1) coordinate lookup thereafter
- Sorted coordinate list for binary search navigation
- next_populated / prev_populated jump to nearest content
- Dimension extent queries for density analysis
- coordinates_matching predicate filter
- ScrollSpan stores byte offsets (start, end) for mmap integrationR1.1 -- Memory-Mapped I/O
The editor's I/O foundation. Memory-map phext files and build LatticeIndex over raw bytes.R1.1.1 -- MappedLattice
- Memory-map phext files read-only via memmap2
- Copy-on-write overlay: HashMap<Coordinate, ScrollOverlay>
- Three states: Modified(String), Deleted, Inserted(String)
- Byte-perfect roundtrip reconstruction on save
- read_scroll: check overlay first, fallback to mmap span
- write_scroll: edits go to overlay, mmap never modified
- save: reconstruct from mmap spans + overlay deltas, re-mmap, rebuild index
- 4MB file = 4MB virtual address space, not heapR1.3 -- Navigator
The cursor model for 9D phext navigation. The 'mind' of Lattice mode.R1.3.1 -- Navigator
- 9D cursor tracking current coordinate
- Active dimension selection (1-9 keys)
- Forward/backward movement with lower dimension reset
- Marks stack for position bookmarks
- History with back/forward navigation
- next_populated / prev_populated via index binary searchR1.3.2 -- Intra-Scroll Cursor
- Position: (line, col) 0-indexed
- Selection: start/end with direction
- from_offset / to_offset conversion
- Word-boundary navigation
- Sticky column across vertical moves
- Bridge between Lattice mode and Edit modeR1.4 -- Search
- Full-text search across all scrolls
- Returns coordinates, not byte offsets
- Parallel via rayon for files > 512KB, serial for smaller
- Case-insensitive by default
- Atomic early termination at max_results
- Context extraction (40 chars around match)
- search_lattice_auto picks parallel vs serialR1.5 -- Topology
Sentron neural topology and lattice statistics.R1.5.1 -- Sentron
- 2x4 connections per neuron (fwd + bwd x 4 axes)
- 5x8 neurons per sentron (40 total)
- Manhattan distance ordering from cursor
- 8 dims: structural (Library/Shelf/Series/Collection) + sequential (Volume/Book/Chapter/Section)
- Scroll is the neuron center
- Sub-millisecond rebuildR1.6 -- Statistics
- ScrollStats: byte_size, line_count, word_count, char_count
- DimensionDensity: distribution of scroll counts per dimension value
- Sparkline rendering
- Neighborhood: populated coords near cursor
- LatticeOverview: total scrolls, total bytes, dimension extentsR1.7-R1.9 -- Editor Framework
Pluggable editing modes. Sits between navigator and mode.R1.7 -- Editor Mode Trait
- Pluggable EditorMode trait
- EditKey abstraction: code, ctrl, alt, shift
- EditResult: Nothing | CursorMoved | TextChanged | ExitEdit | Status
- CursorStyle: Block, Line, Underline
- Framework-independentR1.9 -- Vim Mode
- Sub-modes: Normal, Insert, Visual, Command
- Count prefix for repeat
- Motions: h/l/j/k/w/b/e/0/$
- Operators: d/c/y
- Multi-key: dd, dw, yy
- Insert: i/a/o/O
- Command: :w, :q, :wqR-UML6D -- 6D UML Semantic Layer
- Map collection dimension to SDLC phases (Meta through Training)
- 5D artifact addresses (volume.book.chapter/section.scroll)
- Phase enum with name, short code, and color
- ArtifactAddr extraction from full coordinates
- Trace: walk all phases at a fixed 5D address
- UmlContext: phase + artifact for any coordinate
- Runtime-configurable phase assignments via Meta
- Structural traceability: same 5D address across collectionsR1.8 -- Undo/Redo
- Per-scroll undo/redo stacks
- EditOp: Insert, Delete, Replace
- Phext serialization in .work.phext
- x.chapter = edit sequence number
- Edit history is navigable phextR-TTS -- Coordinate Pronunciation
- 3x5x17+1 syllable system
- X: Onset (open/voiced/unvoiced)
- Y: Vowel (a/e/i/o/u)
- Z: Coda (17 terminations)
- Zero = 'om'
- SSML output for TTS enginesR3 -- Web UI
HTTP-served phext editor. Zero-framework architecture.R3.1 -- phext-edit
- Raw TcpListener, no framework
- Embedded SPA (HTML/CSS/JS)
- REST JSON API
- Thread-per-connection, Arc<Mutex<AppState>>
- Sentron panel, navtree, search, edit mode
- Coordinate hyperlinking
- Dark theme, keyboard navigation
- Auth token, directory mode
- URL hash for shareable positionsR3.7 -- uml6d-edit
- Extends phext-edit with SDLC awareness
- Phase badge (color-coded)
- 5D artifact address display
- Trace panel: all 9 phases at current 5D address
- Phase picker (p key)
- Quick-nav: r=REQ d=DES s=SRC x=TST
- POST /api/phase endpoint
- Phase-colored navtree labelsCore Module Design
Coordinate extensions and lattice index form the foundation.@startuml coordinate_ext
enum Dimension {
  Scroll = 1
  Section = 2
  Chapter = 3
  Book = 4
  Volume = 5
  Collection = 6
  Series = 7
  Shelf = 8
  Library = 9
  +from_index(i: u8): Option<Dimension>
  +name(): &str
  +delimiter(): u8
}

trait CoordinateNav {
  +navigate_forward(dim): bool
  +navigate_backward(dim): bool
  +dimension_value(dim): usize
  +set_dimension(dim, value)
  +with_dimension(dim, value): Coordinate
}

Coordinate ..|> CoordinateNav
@enduml@startuml index
class ScrollSpan {
  +start: usize
  +end: usize
}

class LatticeIndex {
  -entries: HashMap<Coordinate, ScrollSpan>
  -ordered: Vec<Coordinate>
  +build(buffer: &[u8]): LatticeIndex
  +get(coord): Option<&ScrollSpan>
  +contains(coord): bool
  +scroll_count(): usize
  +next_populated(coord): Option<Coordinate>
  +prev_populated(coord): Option<Coordinate>
  +dimension_extent(dim): Vec<usize>
}

LatticeIndex --> ScrollSpan
@endumlStorage Module Design
Memory-mapped I/O with copy-on-write overlay.@startuml mmap
enum ScrollOverlay {
  Modified(String)
  Deleted
  Inserted(String)
}

class MappedLattice {
  -mmap: Mmap
  -index: LatticeIndex
  -overlay: HashMap<Coordinate, ScrollOverlay>
  +open(path): MappedLattice
  +read_scroll(coord): Option<String>
  +write_scroll(coord, content)
  +has_scroll(coord): bool
  +save()
  +to_phext_bytes(): Vec<u8>
  +index(): &LatticeIndex
}

MappedLattice --> LatticeIndex
MappedLattice --> ScrollOverlay
@endumlNavigation Module Design
9D cursor model with history, marks, and populated-jump.@startuml navigator
class Navigator {
  -position: Coordinate
  -active_dimension: Dimension
  -marks: Vec<Coordinate>
  -history: Vec<Coordinate>
  +new(): Navigator
  +position(): Coordinate
  +select_dimension(index: u8)
  +move_forward()
  +move_backward()
  +goto(coord)
  +next_populated(index)
  +prev_populated(index)
  +push_mark()
  +pop_mark()
}

Navigator --> Coordinate
Navigator --> Dimension
@enduml@startuml cursor
class Position {
  +line: usize
  +col: usize
  +from_offset(text, offset): Position
  +to_offset(text): usize
}

class ScrollCursor {
  -position: Position
  -selection: Option<Selection>
  -sticky_col: usize
  +move_left/right/up/down(text)
  +word_forward/backward(text)
}

ScrollCursor --> Position
@enduml@startuml search
class SearchHit {
  +coordinate: Coordinate
  +offset: usize
  +length: usize
  +context: String
}

class SearchEngine <<functions>> {
  +search_lattice(buffer, index, pattern): Vec<SearchHit>
  +search_lattice_parallel(...): Vec<SearchHit>
  +search_lattice_auto(...): Vec<SearchHit>
  +search_coordinates(index, pattern): Vec<Coordinate>
}

note: Parallel threshold 512KB, context 40 chars, rayon
@endumlTopology Module Design
Sentron neural topology and lattice statistics.@startuml sentron
enum AxisGroup { Structural, Sequential }

class Axon {
  +dimension: Dimension
  +group: AxisGroup
  +backward_count: usize
  +forward_count: usize
}

class Sentron {
  +center: Coordinate
  +structural_reach: usize
  +sequential_reach: usize
  +build(pos, index): Sentron
  +size(): usize
  +structural_axons(): &[Axon]
  +sequential_axons(): &[Axon]
}

note: 40 neurons max, 8 axons, Manhattan distance
Sentron --> Axon
@enduml@startuml stats
class ScrollStats {
  +byte_size, line_count, word_count, char_count
  +from_bytes(bytes): ScrollStats
}

class DimensionDensity {
  +dimension: Dimension
  +distribution: Vec<(usize, usize)>
  +sparkline(width): String
}

class LatticeOverview {
  +total_scrolls, total_bytes
  +build(buffer, index): LatticeOverview
}
@endumlEditor Module Design
Pluggable editing modes with vim as default.@startuml editor
trait EditorMode {
  +handle_key(key, ctx): EditResult
  +cursor_style(): CursorStyle
  +status_text(): String
}

enum EditResult { Nothing, CursorMoved, TextChanged, ExitEdit, Status(String) }
enum CursorStyle { Block, Line, Underline }

class EditContext {
  +text: String
  +cursor: ScrollCursor
  +undo: UndoEngine
}

VimMode ..|> EditorMode
@enduml@startuml vim
enum VimSubMode { Normal, Insert, Visual, Command }

class VimMode {
  -sub_mode: VimSubMode
  -pending: String
  -count: Option<usize>
