Track known issues and fixes. Each entry links to the commit.Quick Start Guide

1. Build: cargo build --bin uml6d-edit
2. Run: uml6d-edit file.phext [--port 8080]
3. Navigate: 1-9 dim, h/l move, j/k jump, p phase, e edit
4. Phase keys: r=REQ d=DES s=SRC x=TST
5. Trace panel: T key
6. Save: Ctrl+SCoordinate Guide

Full 9D: z.z.z/y.y.y/x.x.x
  series.shelf.library / collection.volume.book / chapter.section.scroll

6D UML inner 6:
  collection=Phase, volume=Sprint, book=Module,
  chapter=Component, section=File, scroll=Unit

5D artifact address: volume.book.chapter/section.scroll

Example: 1.1.1/4.1.2/3.1.1
  = Source (4), Sprint 1, Module 2, Component 3, File 1, Unit 1
  Requirement: 1.1.1/2.1.2/3.1.1  Test: 1.1.1/5.1.2/3.1.1Architecture

Layer 1: Core types (coordinate_ext, index)
Layer 2: Storage (mmap + copy-on-write)
Layer 3: Navigation (navigator, cursor)
Layer 4: Intelligence (search, sentron, stats)
Layer 5: Editing (editor modes, undo)
Layer 6: Semantics (uml6d)
Layer 7: Presentation (web UI, TUI)

Dependencies flow downward. UML6D adds SDLC meaning
without modifying lower layers.Storage docsNav docsSearch docsTopology docsEditor docsUML6D docsUndo docsTTS docsWeb UI docsPhext: Hierarchical Digital Memory

Phext extends plain text to 11 dimensions via ASCII control codes.
Line breaks (0x0A) give 2D; phext adds 7 more delimiter levels.
Enables petabyte-scale organization in a single file.

ASCII defined 0x01-0x1F in the 1960s. Most fell out of use.
Phext reclaims them as dimensional delimiters.

Performance: modern SSDs write 2 GB/sec but file abstractions
haven't evolved since 25 KB/sec era. Phext eliminates
filesystem overhead for structured data.Sentron: Neural Topology for 9D Navigation

40 neurons (nearest populated coords) form a cortical column.
8 axons per center (4 structural + 4 sequential).
Each measures backward/forward reachability.

Rebuilt sub-millisecond on every navigation event.
Provides real-time topological awareness.6D UML: Structural Traceability via Dimensional Addressing

Traditional traceability matrices annotate links between
requirements, design, code, and tests. Annotations are fragile.

6D UML makes the coordinate system the traceability matrix.
An artifact's 5D address is stable across all SDLC phases.
Collection selects the phase.

Walking collection 2 to 4 at same 5D address traces
requirement to implementation. No links to maintain.
The structure IS the relationship.Onboarding: Your First 6D UML Session

Step 1: Look at the top bar
  - Colored badge = current SDLC phase
  - 9D coordinate = exact position
  - 5D address = artifact identity

Step 2: Navigate
  1-9 select dimension, h/l move, j/k jump populated

Step 3: Phase navigation
  p = phase picker, or quick keys: r/d/s/x

Step 4: Trace panel
  T = show all 9 phases for current artifact
  Filled = content exists, empty = not yet written

Step 5: Edit
  e = edit mode, Ctrl+S = saveCore Concepts

1. Phext: plain text extended to 11D via ASCII delimiters
2. Scroll: basic unit of content
3. Coordinate: 9D address (z.z.z/y.y.y/x.x.x)
4. Collection: SDLC phase dimension
5. 5D Address: artifact identity across phases
6. Trace: walking artifact across all phases
7. Sentron: local topology
8. Phase: one of 9 SDLC stages
9. Module: a book in 5D space
10. Component: a chapter within a module